# Per-Dockerfile .dockerignore for the sign extension (Go build).
# Build context is the sign extension dir itself (extensions/sign/). The Go
# Dockerfile only needs the go/ module — tee-node is fetched from the network
# during `go mod download`, so nothing else has to enter the build context.

# Ignore everything, then re-include just the Go module.
*
!go/

# Generated bindings, the dev-machine tooling module, and build output aren't
# needed to compile ./cmd/docker.
go/tools

# Heavy / vendored / generated (in case any slip under go/)
**/node_modules
**/out
**/vendor

# IDE / VCS / OS noise
**/.git
**/.idea
**/.vscode
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db
**/.claude

# Logs / temp files
**/*.log
**/*.tmp
**/*.swp
**/*.swo
